            Kamuthi: The world's largest solar power project
            The world's largest solar power park is located in the Kamuthi in the Indian state of Tamil Nadu.Spread over 2,500 acres (10 sq km, 3.9 sq miles) and consisting of 2.5m solar panels, Kamuthi is estimated to make enough power for 750,000 people.BBC Click's David Reid reports.See more at Click's website and @BBCClick.
                
                        24 May 2017
                    
                
        
